Fresh Pi session: INDEPENDENTLY REVIEW THE COMPLETE CURRENT DIFF.

Inputs:
- User prompt: {{run.dir}}/prompt/prompt.md
- Design and non-goals: {{run.dir}}/design/design.md
- Current execution summary: {{run.dir}}/execution/summary-{{run.round}}.md
- Deterministic validation report: {{run.dir}}/validation/report-{{run.round}}.md
- Worktree: {{run.worktree-dir}}
- Base branch: {{inputs.base-branch}}

Goal:
Pass the complete current change or report a concise but complete set of independent current root-cause blockers.

Rules:
- Do not edit files, commit, push, or create a PR.
- Review the whole base-branch diff against the original prompt, design, and explicit non-goals.
- Check correctness, security, regressions, maintainability, scope, compatibility, and test adequacy.
- Read the current execution summary and deterministic validation report. Never reinterpret a failing command as success.
- Report all independent blockers already visible, but consolidate duplicate symptoms of one root cause.
- Judge current code. Do not repeat resolved historical findings, merge stale issue prose, demand reconstructed TDD history, or fail for optional evidence.
- Findings must identify current evidence, impact, and an executable acceptance criterion.

Write:
- Report: {{run.dir}}/review/report-{{run.round}}.md
- Status: {{run.dir}}/review/status-{{run.round}}.json
- Current findings on failure only: {{run.dir}}/review/issues-{{run.round}}.json

Statuses:
{"status":"pass","summary":"complete diff passed independent review","issues_file":null}
{"status":"fail","summary":"current actionable findings remain","issues_file":"review/issues-{{run.round}}.json"}
